other_tests.procedure_name: CT ABDOMEN AND PELVIS WITH CONTRAST
other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated, demonstrates mural edema, measuring up to 1.3 cm, with adjacent fat stranding, compatible with acute uncomplicated appendicitis. The left kidney shows subtle hypoenhancement compared to the right kidney, with cortical scarring at the upper pole and multiple subcentimeter cysts in the lower pole.
